[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has 17 points, counting 1 for the fifth Club. She has a balanced distribution 
so she opens 1NT.

NORTH is also balanced, so he does the math. SOUTH has either 15, 16 or 17, and with NORTH's 
18 the partnership total is either 33, 34 or 35. That is enough for a small slam, but 
below the 37 points needed for Grand Slam so he bids 6NT.}

